The 'YO YO Endurance Test' provides an important instrument for determining the level of physical efficiency of an athlete.
The physical capacity is evaluated quickly and easily by placing two cones spaced 20 meters each other.
The athlete has to run at full speed from one cone to another and then return again on the first cone. This path must be repeated for six times without any break, and get  the split times every time the athlete passes on the first cone.

This application will track all the split time and at the end will be calculated two parameters that determine the outcome of the test. More these values are low and better will be the athlete's performance.

Basically the final result is given by a mathematical formula that processes the delta between the averages of the last two split times and the first two split times  and thereby the athlete's ability to maintain its maximum speed for a certain period of time.

The second value obtained on completion of the test, is the first result considering also the total time of the test.

The 'YO YO Endurance Test' can be used to determine the level of athletic in all sports (football, running, basketball, volleyball, cycling, tennis etc.)
At the end of the test you can get for each athlete the final result (eg. "Above average" or "Poor") and the Vo2Max estimate

How does it work?

To record a punch, grip iPhone tightly and punch. App records a punch motion at the inertial frame of reference using gyroscope and accelerometer data and saves the punch.
All information about a punch is revealed now.
Graph of speed and all the punch rates: acceleration, distance, power, duration, reaction time.
On speed graph you can see how your punch accelerates and swing as first peak if it exists.
You can record another punch to make a comparison, or you can share your punch.
You can choose appropriate units: kilograms or pounds, kilometers per hour or meters per second and etc.

Technical data:

On iPhone 4S application can’t work properly. Punch speed on iPhone 4S may be 2 times lower, but duration and reaction time are still correct. App works perfectly on iPhone 5, iPhone 5s, iPhone 6, iPhone 6 Plus, iPhone 6S, iPhone 6S Plus, iPhone SE. But it may be not that easy to grip iPhone 6 Plus or  iPhone 6S Plus when you punch.

Speed measurement error is not more than 5% in most cases. Maximum acceleration is about 16g. Power is calculated approximately, with special formula based on your skills level, punch speed, and your mass. Put your mass in a punch to get more accurate result. Distance is calculated with small deviation when you punch the air. You get a straight distance between punch starting point and punch ending point. Time accuracy is limited to 10 ms.
